    October 17, 2015

    A Call to Conscience “Dared to Imagine” at the Julia Davis Branch Library Thursday, October 15! The poem, Let America Be America Again” by Langston Hughes was performed in four voices by Call to Conscience staff Peggy Calvin, Linda Nance, Lavelle Wilkins-Chinn and audience member Connie (video coming soon). Call to Conscience board member, Shirley LeFlore was there to encourage the flow of creativity! Inspired by Langston’s poem, we imagined America in 2035 by creating collages, building structures using found and recycled objects, and writing poetry and writing “new "legislation” for a new, enlightened America.

    #DaretoImagine with fellows, artists-in-residents and commisioned artists of The Laundromat Project. These artists, makers, and cultural workers discussed the role arts & culture in anti-gentrification organizing in NYC. They then transported themselves to the year 2035 and wrote letters to a loved one explaining what role they played to help combat gentrification and #SaveNYC Thanks Laundromat Project!
